# Output Variables

## Overview
The following output values are generated after the successful deployment of the Compute infrastructure.

## EC2 Outputs

| Output | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| EC2 Instance ID | Unique identifier of the EC2 instance |
| EC2 Public IP | Public IP address of the EC2 instance |
| EC2 Private IP | Private IP address of the EC2 instance |

## Launch Template Outputs

| Output | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| Launch Template ID | Unique ID of the Launch Template |
| Launch Template Name | Name of the Launch Template |

## Auto Scaling Group Outputs

| Output | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| Auto Scaling Group Name | Name of the Auto Scaling Group |
| Desired Capacity | Desired number of EC2 instances |
| Running Instances | Number of active EC2 instances |

## Application Load Balancer Outputs

| Output | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| Load Balancer ARN | Amazon Resource Name of the ALB |
| Load Balancer DNS Name | DNS name used to access the application |
| Load Balancer Zone ID | Hosted Zone ID of the ALB |

## Listener Outputs

| Output | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| Listener ARN | Amazon Resource Name of the Listener |
| Listener Port | Listener port number |

## Target Group Outputs

| Output | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| Target Group ARN | Amazon Resource Name of the Target Group |
| Healthy Targets | Number of healthy registered targets |

## Amazon RDS Outputs

| Output | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| RDS Endpoint | Endpoint used to connect to the database |
| Database Name | Name of the database |
| Database Port | Database connection port |

## Purpose
These output values provide important information about the deployed AWS infrastructure, allowing users to access the application, connect to the database, and verify the deployed resources.
